#CircuitBreakerSG D-36

We're having one of our favourite fish tonight; Pan-fried Salmon with homemade Teriyaki Sauce. Love the crispy skin most.

The next dish is another family's favourite; Chinese Sausage with golden Garlic bits. Render the fats from the Lup Cheong first before adding in the minced garlic. Dish out once the garlic is crispy. Do give it a try!

Lastly Napa Cabbage with Wood Fungus.

Enjoy your #dinner too 💝
.

@tet_chu First time someone is eating it the same way as us 🙌
@yvonnemsw it is actually really tasty. We also steamed it with chopped garlic
Yummy dinner... our family and wed to eat the lup cheong this way too
@f1leng2 Thanks Leng! Pan fry the skin side on a heated pan. Making sure it's dry. Let it fry till crisp before flipping to the other side.
I love your salmon 😘. How do you fry till so crispy and nice?
@yvonnemsw I see. I find this veg v blend of stir fry in norm way. Any tips to improve on taste?
@baking_with_double_grace Add seasoning & stock. I seldom buy this vegetable but the family likes it. They said 很甜
@yvonnemsw my family finds it bland, tasteless. 😅
Yvonne, your fish looks v yummy, I bake it in small oven toaster then drizzle with home made sauce, it’s the lazy way. 😅  Can I ask for the napa, is it 娃娃菜？
@maya__8888 My teriyaki sauce consists of 2 tbsp Soya Sauce, 2 tbsp Mirin, 2 tbsp Sake, 1 tbsp sugar & 50ml water. Cook till thickened.
Beautiful spread! How do u make the teriyaki sauce?
@crystal_seasalt Pan fry the skin-side on a heated pan using medium low. Make sure the skin is dry. Let it fry till crisp before flipping to the other side.
can you teach me how to get crispy golden pan fried fish like this?  do I need to keep it at medium heat?

Your dinner always looks so beautiful and delicious.
Love the salmon 😋😋😋
